      <pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/dbic-vs-dbio/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;disclaimer-image-is-generated-using-chatgpt&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DISCLAIMER:&lt;/strong&gt; Image is generated using &lt;code&gt;ChatGPT&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;While I have been writing the manuscript for my upcoming book on &lt;code&gt;DBIx::Class&lt;/code&gt;, I must admit that I haven’t dedicated all of my focus to it. Everywhere I look I see something new and interesting and have been easily distracted. For example, just the other day I noticed that there is a new player in the &lt;code&gt;Perl ORM&lt;/code&gt; space named &lt;code&gt;DBIO&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you are not familiar with what I am talking about, I suggest that you take a moment to investigate &lt;a href=&#34;https://metacpan.org/pod/DBIO&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DBIO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; more closely.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
